&nbsp;

And thats all for the probaly last update i do in this strategy, GLHF!

The strategy is simple. Quickly get out Mirrorjade and have a few other fusions to back him up. I am still fairly new to the Despia deck so I can't make some crazy amount of combos and stuff you can do with the deck like I have done with my other deck lists on this site so feel free to look and change whatever you feel is necessary for your playstyle and what you are looking for. I am just using cards I think are underrated in the deck and are actually way better than they seem. I am also playing some of the newer cards like Albaz the Ashen because I think the card will be really good when it comes out and also because it has the main deck Albion effect of having its name be treated as Fallen of Albaz.

&nbsp;

That is al for the summery. I hope you enjoy the deck and remember- ALBAZ AND BRANDED/DESPIA DESERVED THE MANGA TREATMENT AND NOT SKY STRIKER UGH!!!

