&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

P.u.n.k is being used as engine for <a data-name="Chaos Ruler">Chaos Ruler</a>, <a data-name="Meliae of the Trees">Meliae of the Trees</a>, <a data-name="Auroradon">Auroradon</a> and rank 8's. Therion is just taking full advantage of that.

&nbsp;

1.5 card combo: <a data-name="Ogre Dance">Ogre Dance</a> + any discard.

Activate Ogre Dance adding <a data-name="Ze amin">Ze amin</a>~ Normal summon Ze Amin~ Activate its effect and add <a data-name="Foxy Tune">Foxy Tune</a>~ Activate Foxy sending other card from your hand to special summon <a data-name="Dia Note">Dia Note</a> from your deck ~Synchro summon <a data-name="Chaos Ruler">Chaos Ruler</a> ~chain 1 Chaos ruler effect and chain 2 Dia Note ~Dia Note summons back Ze Amin and Chaos Ruler mills 5 and add one dark or light ~link summon <a data-name="Halqifibrax">Halqifibrax</a> ~halq summon <a data-name="001">001</a> from deck ~Link summon <a data-name="Auroradon">Auroradon</a> ~summon tokens, summon 001 back ~Synchro summon <a data-name="Cupid Pitch">Cupid Pitch</a> ~Cupid effect to rise its level by 1 ~now, if you wanna make Borreload Savage you just summon its directly, but if you wanna shenshen you need to synchro summon Accel Synchro Stardust and then use its effect to summon back 001 ~Independent of what you've chosen, you used cupid pitch so you can search for <a data-name="Destiny Hero - Plasma">Destiny Hero - Plasma</a> ~Chaos ruler second effect, banish Ogre Dance and Cupid from gy to special summon itself ~Tribute Auroradon, his last token and Chaos ruler to special summon Plasma. Also, if you wanted to summon shenshen, it has to be the last summon, otherwise you would banish Auroradon that can be used later for Accesscode pops or Borreload. The reason why im not using <a data-name="Coltwing">Coltwing</a> is because it is not only another brick but also raises the chance of milling a key card with Chaos Ruler (that last part also applies to 001, so i might add more xyz's as a plan b).

&nbsp;

P.u.n.k Therion, to me, is the best therion variant.

