First turn you want to summon DPE, Winda, or Dark Law using Mask Change 2. That limits special summons and graveyard plays. However, there are enough fusion cards and diverse monsters to go into what the situation requires. First Darklord is a big body that prevents effects that target dark fairies (IE Main-deck Despia and Scythe and Dark Honest). Mysterion is good for superpoly, can out dragons and spellcasters, as are both Predaplant fusion monsters, who not only out fusion and dark monsters using super poly, but have good negation effects. Levianeer is a good free summon that can thin hands, and Shaddoll Dragon is for making Winda and for using as material since it lets you pop a backrow. Because I'm running so many spells, Engage and Widow Anchor. Two Crossouts and a suite of handtraps to both use or negate with Crossout.

&nbsp;

(Note: Ignore the boss monster bar, it doesn't represent the deck. There is no way to edit them.)

Usual combo starting with Lubellion depending on the hand you can search the Branded Lost and have an interruption end board with Mercourier in hand. Allure as the drawing power and Tragedy / Mercourier as the cost. Still testing but I like the ratios and the hands 3/5 times are playable going first. Going second requires understanding of the deck and proper use of bait tactics. Some side cards were added for testing the newer cards from OCG.

&nbsp;

Best hand possible so far has been Allure, Tragedy, Branded Lost OR Fusion, Veiler, Upstart.

Allure can pitch almost anything for pluses and odds of you getting the cards in hand to combo are pretty good ratio wise. Sadly its not perfect.

&nbsp;

Searchers: Aluber, Kitt, Tragedy, Mercourier, Branded Opening.

Draw Power: Allure, Pot of P (debating subbing it out), Upstart, Tactics

Negates: Mercourier, Veiler, Dark Ruler, Called by

&nbsp;

This deck is probably gonna be reuploaded a few times to see how I can tweak it, but I like this build so far.
